# Subscription Billing Workflow Restructure

## Problem

[CreateDraftInvoicesActivity](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/subscription/update_billing_period_activities.go#96-129) calls [CreateDraftInvoiceForSubscription](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/subscription.go#5759-5793), which **returns `nil` for zero-amount periods** (line 5781 of [subscription.go](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/subscription.go)). This means zero-dollar periods are silently dropped, causing missed invoices and no auditability.

[ProcessInvoiceWorkflow](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/workflows/invoice/process_invoice_workflow.go#21-125) today just does Finalize → Sync → Pay with no usage calculation step.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. New `InvoiceStatusSkipped` status

#### [MODIFY] [invoice.go (types)](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/types/invoice.go)

Add a new constant alongside `DRAFT`, `FINALIZED`, `VOIDED`:
```go
// InvoiceStatusSkipped indicates a zero-usage invoice that was intentionally skipped.
// No invoice number is assigned and no payment is attempted.
InvoiceStatusSkipped InvoiceStatus = "SKIPPED"
```

- Add `InvoiceStatusSkipped` to the [Validate()](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/models/subscription_billing.go#33-50) allowed list.

---

### 2. Zero-Dollar Placeholder Draft Invoice Creation

#### [MODIFY] [subscription.go (CreateDraftInvoiceForSubscription)](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/subscription.go)

**Current behavior:** Returns `nil, nil` if `invoiceReq.Subtotal.IsZero()`.

**New behavior:** Always call `invoiceService.CreateInvoice(ctx, *invoiceReq)` — even when subtotal is zero. The request will produce a valid `draft` invoice with `amount = 0`, no line items, and no invoice number.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The [CreateInvoice](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#117-307) method already handles generating invoice numbers. We need to **skip invoice number generation** when subtotal is zero. One approach: pass `InvoiceNumber: lo.ToPtr("")` (empty) in the request when zero, and guard the number generation inside [CreateInvoice](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#117-307). Alternatively, add a `SkipInvoiceNumber bool` option to [CreateInvoiceRequest](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/billing.go#65-67). Preferred approach: **Add `SkipInvoiceNumber bool` to `dto.CreateInvoiceRequest`** and gate the number-generation block in [CreateInvoice](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#117-307) on it.

Concretely, [PrepareSubscriptionInvoiceRequest](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/billing.go#1526-1741) (in [billing.go](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/billing.go)) will be updated to set `SkipInvoiceNumber = true` when subtotal is zero.

#### [MODIFY] [billing.go (PrepareSubscriptionInvoiceRequest)](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/billing.go)

When the resulting [CreateInvoiceRequest](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/billing.go#65-67) has a zero subtotal, set `SkipInvoiceNumber = true` and include **no line items**.

#### [MODIFY] [dto/invoice.go](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/api/dto/invoice.go) *(if needed)*

Add `SkipInvoiceNumber bool` to [CreateInvoiceRequest](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/billing.go#65-67).

#### [MODIFY] [invoice.go (service CreateInvoice)](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go)

Gate the invoice number generation block (step 4) behind `!req.SkipInvoiceNumber`.

---

### 3. New `CalculateInvoiceActivity` in [ProcessInvoiceWorkflow](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/workflows/invoice/process_invoice_workflow.go#21-125)

#### [MODIFY] [invoice_activities.go](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/invoice/invoice_activities.go)

Add a new activity `CalculateInvoiceActivity`:
- Loads the invoice (and its subscription).
- Calls `billingService.PrepareSubscriptionInvoiceRequest(ctx, sub, periodStart, periodEnd, ReferencePointPeriodEnd)` to get the full charged amount.
- **If usage/amount == 0**: marks invoice status as `SKIPPED` (via a new `InvoiceService.SkipInvoice(ctx, id)` method or inline repo update). Returns `{Skipped: true}`.
- **If usage/amount > 0**:
  - Creates/replaces line items on the invoice (using an `UpdateInvoiceLineItems` approach or re-running [CreateInvoice](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#117-307) with the existing ID).
  - Assigns an invoice number (calls `InvoiceRepo.GetNextInvoiceNumber`).
  - Returns `{Skipped: false}`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Design Decision**: The simplest approach is to add a new service method `InvoiceService.CalculateAndPopulateInvoice(ctx, invoiceID)` that:
> 1. Fetches the invoice + subscription.
> 2. Calls billing service to calculate all charges.
> 3. If zero: updates status → `SKIPPED`, returns skipped=true.
> 4. If non-zero: adds line items, assigns invoice number, updates draft record.

#### Models: add `CalculateInvoiceActivityInput/Output`

#### [MODIFY] [process_invoice.go (models)](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/models/invoice/process_invoice.go)

Add:
```go
type CalculateInvoiceActivityInput struct {
    InvoiceID     string
    TenantID      string
    EnvironmentID string
    UserID        string
}

type CalculateInvoiceActivityOutput struct {
    Skipped bool
    Amount  decimal.Decimal
}
```

---

### 4. Update [ProcessInvoiceWorkflow](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/workflows/invoice/process_invoice_workflow.go#21-125)

#### [MODIFY] [process_invoice_workflow.go](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/workflows/invoice/process_invoice_workflow.go)

New step ordering:
1. **STEP 1**: `CalculateInvoiceActivity` — compute usage, populate line items, assign invoice number, or mark skipped.
2. **If `output.Skipped == true`**: return early — no finalize, no sync, no payment.
3. **STEP 2**: [FinalizeInvoiceActivity](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/invoice/invoice_activities.go#29-59)
4. **STEP 3**: [SyncInvoiceToVendorActivity](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/invoice/invoice_activities.go#60-90)
5. **STEP 4**: [AttemptInvoicePaymentActivity](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/invoice/invoice_activities.go#91-121)

Add a new constant:
```go
ActivityCalculateInvoice = "CalculateInvoiceActivity"
```

---

### 5. [CreateDraftInvoicesActivity](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/subscription/update_billing_period_activities.go#96-129) always returns IDs

#### [MODIFY] [update_billing_period_activities.go](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/subscription/update_billing_period_activities.go)

Remove the `if invoice != nil` guard — always append the invoice ID to the list, since we no longer return `nil` for zero-amount invoices.

