## Key Design Decisions for Discussion

> [!NOTE]
> **Q1 — Where does `CalculateAndPopulateInvoice` live?**
> Proposed: as a new [InvoiceService](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#32-64) method, so it can be tested independently and reused outside Temporal.

> [!NOTE]
> **Q2 — Line item replacement strategy**
> Since the zero-dollar draft has no line items, we can simply call `InvoiceRepo.CreateWithLineItems` after deleting the old empty invoice — OR add a new `UpdateLineItems` repo method. Which do you prefer?

> [!NOTE]
> **Q3 — Invoice number assignment on populate**
> Currently `GetNextInvoiceNumber` is called during [CreateInvoice](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#117-307). For the new flow we'd call it during `CalculateAndPopulateInvoice`. Should we call it only at populate time (recommended), or pre-assign and then void/reclaim on skip?

> [!NOTE]
> **Q4 — [performFinalizeInvoiceActions](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#642-663) guard**
> Currently it checks `inv.InvoiceStatus != DRAFT` and errors. We need to ensure `SKIPPED` invoices never reach [FinalizeInvoice](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/service/invoice.go#38-39) (handled by early return in workflow).

---

## Verification Plan

### Build check
```bash
cd /Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice && go build ./...
```

### Unit tests (existing)
```bash
cd /Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice && go test ./internal/service/... -run TestBilling -v
cd /Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice && go test ./internal/service/... -run TestInvoice -v
```

### Manual verification
1. Trigger a subscription with no usage for the period — confirm the invoice is created with status `SKIPPED`, amount = 0, no invoice number.
2. Trigger a subscription with usage for the period — confirm the invoice transitions: `DRAFT` → calculated with line items + invoice number → `FINALIZED` → payment attempted.
3. Confirm [CreateDraftInvoicesActivity](file:///Users/hiteshshimpi/Desktop/Work/flexprice/internal/temporal/activities/subscription/update_billing_period_activities.go#96-129) always returns an invoice ID even for zero-dollar periods.
